    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-26T19:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="1257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/635</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Antwerp</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DHW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Diederich</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Antwerp</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-08-26T19:20:00-05:00"
                        notBefore="1914-08-26T00:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                    </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 26, 1914, 7:20 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Your cables 22, 23, 25 August, welfare.<note n="1" xml:id="d1257fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> All communications Belgium save. Ghent, Bruges, and seacoast
                    cut off. Gibson, after two days’ sojourn here, has started back to Brussels this
                    noon. Hope he will get safely through firing lines. Antwerp very calm though
                    almost completely isolated. At outbreak of war excitement was at fever heat and
                    though many German women and children were made to endure cruel hardships by the
                    perhaps too precipitate execution of the expulsion order no bodily harm or
                    injury was done them. I know whereof I speak. In times like these stories of
                    horrible atrocities will crop out everywhere but let Americans keep cool and
                    remember <hi rend="italic">audiatur et altera pars</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DHW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Diederich</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
